<dl id="n05028b"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n05" href="#n05028b">N05 (VI.B.2)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n05all.htm#n05028b"> 28(b)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> execution (&dagger;)</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">To <font color="green">[Paul]</font> it was the <mark>death</mark> and resurrection, not the life and teaching, <mark>of Christ</mark> that supremely mattered; and so he raised the tragedy of the Calvary into the domain of mysteries, treating it as a lost and ruined world&apos;s sole hope of deliverance. <small> J.T. Lloyd, <a name="GODE" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#GODE"><cite title="source">God-Eating</cite></a>, (1921) 10-3</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
